boundary value problem (1)-(5) by Weyl function and spectral data.

We consider the boundary value problem $\tilde{L}$ which has the same form
with $L$ but with different coefficients $\tilde{\Omega}(x),$ $\tilde{f}
_{1}\left(  \lambda\right)  ,$ $\tilde{f}_{2}\left(  \lambda\right)
,\tilde{\varepsilon}_{i},\tilde{\theta}_{i},\tilde{\gamma}_{i}$ such that
\newline$\tilde{\Omega}(x)=\left(
